TERMINATION
===============================================================================

1. AUTOMATIC TERMINATION FOR PROHIBITED USE
   Any Prohibited Use immediately and automatically terminates all rights
   granted under this license. No notice from the Licensor is required.
   Termination for Prohibited Use is irrevocable and permanent.

2. TERMINATION FOR OTHER BREACH
   For breaches other than Prohibited Use, the Licensor may terminate this
   license upon written notice to the Licensee. The Licensee has thirty (30)
   days from receipt of notice to cure the breach. If the breach is cured
   within that period, the license is reinstated. If the breach is not cured,
   the license terminates permanently at the end of the cure period.

3. EFFECT OF TERMINATION
   Upon termination, the Licensee must immediately cease all use and
   distribution of the Software and destroy all copies in its possession
   or control. Sections that by their nature should survive termination —
   including Prohibited Use, Warranty Disclaimer, Limitation of Liability,
   and Governing Law — shall survive termination.

